        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks for Thomas Belt’s <hi rend="italic">Naturalist in Nicaragua</hi> [1874], which confirms some of his observations,</p>  
<p>and for <hi rend="italic">Insectivorous plants</hi>, which he praises.</p> 
            <p>Suggests that a book integrating knowledge of plant–animal interactions be written by a Darwinist.</p>
            <p>Defines biology as the science of external interactions.</p>
            <p>German reception is far more positive than Italian.</p>
        </abstract>
